From 0f03c31f2888351bf26847e053e7a3a3886a6a5f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Enrique Parodi Spalazzi <enrique.parodi@airbus.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 00:18:40 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 05/10] feat[core/lang]: evaluate WHERE on empty optionals as
 false

Previously the generated senImplGetFieldValueGetter for an
optional-typed property fell through to throwRuntimeError, which the
object filter caught and used to invalidate the query, so any WHERE
referencing an optional silently never matched.

Now:
- lang::Value carries std::monostate as the empty marker.
- VM comparisons short-circuit to false when either side is empty.
- mathOperation and negate propagate the empty marker.
- Boolean consumers (AND, OR, jumps) treat empty as false.
- The object filter coerces a non-bool interpret result to false so
  a bare WHERE optProp does not crash on std::get<bool>.

Codegen (apps/cli_gen) gains an isOptionalType branch that unwraps via
has_value() + operator* for native, enum, duration, and quantity inner
types. Optional of struct or variant still raises a targeted runtime
error and stays out of scope for now.

Documents the semantics in docs/users_guide/sql.md and exercises them
with a VM-level compiler test plus an end-to-end ObjectFilter test on a
newly added optional property in example_class.
